{"action": "input", "code": "def color_diagonal_line(input_grid: np.ndarray, rect: Tuple[int, int], line_top: Tuple[int, int]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Iterates the diagonal line, starting at the line_top grid. In each iteration, goes right and colors the black grid as the same color of the rectangle until reaching at the same colored grid. Stops iterating until reaching the rect position. Returns the modified input_grid.\n\n    Args:\n    - input_grid (np.ndarray): a 2D numpy array representing a grid of colored squares\n    - rect (Tuple[int, int]): a tuple representing the left-top corner position of a colored rectangle of 4 squares\n    - line_top (Tuple[int, int]): a tuple representing the position of the last colored grid on the diagonal line\n\n    Returns:\n    - np.ndarray: a 2D numpy array representing the modified grid of colored squares\n    \"\"\"\n    i, j = line_top\n    rect_i, rect_j = rect\n    while i <= rect_i and j <= rect_j:\n        if input_grid[i][j] == black:\n            input_grid[i][j] = input_grid[rect_i][rect_j]\n        i += 1\n        j += 1\n    return input_grid\ndef find_colored_rectangles(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a 2D numpy array representing a grid of colored squares, this function finds all colored rectangles of 4 squares\n    and returns their left-top corner positions as a list of tuples.\n\n    Args:\n    - input_grid (np.ndarray): a 2D numpy array representing a grid of colored squares\n\n    Returns:\n    - List[Tuple[int, int]]: a list of tuples representing the left-top corner positions of all colored rectangles of 4 squares\n    \"\"\"\n    rect_positions = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0] - 1):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1] - 1):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == input_grid[i + 1][j] == input_grid[i][j + 1] == input_grid[i + 1][j + 1]:\n                rect_positions.append((i, j))\n    return rect_positions\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    rect_positions = find_colored_rectangles(input_grid)\n    for rect in rect_positions:\n        line_top = find_last_colored_grid(input_grid, rect)\n        input_grid = color_rectangles(input_gird, rect, line_top)\n    return input_grid\ndef color_rectangles(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a 2D numpy array representing a grid of colored squares, this function finds all colored rectangles of 4 squares\n    and colors the black grids in each rectangle with the same color. Returns the modified input_grid.\n\n    Args:\n    - input_grid (np.ndarray): a 2D numpy array representing a grid of colored squares\n\n    Returns:\n    - np.ndarray: a 2D numpy array representing the modified grid of colored squares\n    \"\"\"\n    rect_positions = find_colored_rectangles(input_grid)\n    for rect in rect_positions:\n        line_top = find_last_colored_grid(input_grid, rect)\n        input_grid = color_diagonal_line(input_grid, rect, line_top)\n    return input_grid\ndef find_last_colored_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray, rect: Tuple[int, int]) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Goes diagonally left up from the input rect position, stops until the grid is black. Returns the position of the last colored grid.\n\n    Args:\n    - input_grid (np.ndarray): a 2D numpy array representing a grid of colored squares\n    - rect (Tuple[int, int]): a tuple representing the left-top corner position of a colored rectangle of 4 squares\n\n    Returns:\n    - Tuple[int, int]: a tuple representing the position of the last colored grid\n    \"\"\"\n    i, j = rect\n    while i >= 0 and j >= 0 and (input_grid[i][j] != black):\n        i -= 1\n        j -= 1\n    return (i + 1, j + 1)", "user_code": "def main(input_grid:np.ndarray)->np.ndarray:\n    rect_positions = `find all colored rectangles of 4 squares in the input, return their left-top corner positions`(input_grid)\n    for rect in rect_positions:\n        line_top  = `goes diagonally left u